    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="582"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d582">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.512/2956</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of Mexican Affairs, Department of
                        State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 3, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The Counselor of the Japanese
                    Embassy called this morning and inquired as to the correctness of recent
                    newspaper statements to the effect that early recognition of the Mexican
                    Government by this Government is indicated by the recently published Mexican
                    Executive Decree extending the time within which to make payment of overdue
                    taxes on mining property. I explained to him that this Decree is one that the
                    Mexican authorities have had under consideration for the past year and a half
                    and that I did not understand that any special significance was to be attached
                    to its publication at this time. To his categorical inquiry as to whether the
                    situation had changed, I gave him a copy of your statement of last June<note
                        n="31a" xml:id="d582fn31a">See telegram no. 85, June 8, 1921, to the Chargé
                        in Mexico, <ref target="frus1921v02#pg_406">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1921, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 406</ref>.</note> with the advice that
                    I understood it to be the last public statement of the Department in the
                    matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M[<hi rend="smallcaps">atthew</hi>] E. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >anna</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
